# Canonical line-ending normalisation for this repo.
#
# Without this, Windows checkouts with `core.autocrlf=true` keep flipping every
# source file between LF (what Prettier writes, what Linux/CI expects) and CRLF
# (what Windows checkout produces). The result is `git status` claiming a dozen
# files are modified even when the content diff is empty — a chronic source of
# noise during normal development.
#
# `* text=auto eol=lf` tells git: "treat every text file as text, store it with
# LF in the repository, and convert it to LF on checkout regardless of the OS".
# Binary files are still detected automatically and left alone.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit overrides for binary formats we ship; keeps git from ever trying to
# diff or convert them.
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.ico   binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf   binary
*.otf   binary
*.pdf   binary
